# OSI Model

## The 7 layers

| Layer | Name | What it does | Example |
|-------|------|-------------|---------|
| 7 | Application | Interface for user | HTTP, FTP, DNS |
| 6 | Presentation | Encryption, compression | SSL |
| 5 | Session | Manages sessions | NetBIOS |
| 4 | Transport | End-to-end delivery | TCP, UDP |
| 3 | Network | Routing between networks | IP, OSPF |
| 2 | Data Link | MAC addressing | Ethernet |
| 1 | Physical | Cables and signals | Copper, WiFi |

## TCP vs UDP
- TCP = reliable, slower (HTTP, FTP, SSH)
- UDP = fast, no guarantee (DNS, video, VoIP)
